---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Implementations" description="Known open-source implementations of the Reverse GitOps pattern.">
  <main class="page-main">
    <div class="page-content">
      <h1 class="page-title">Known Implementations</h1>
      <p class="page-lead">
        Open-source projects that implement the Reverse GitOps pattern — a Kubernetes API receives
        user intent, a controller writes it back to Git, a GitOps operator deploys from Git.
      </p>

      <div class="impl-card">
        <div class="impl-header">
          <h2 class="impl-name">gitops-reverser</h2>
          <span class="impl-by">by ConfigButler</span>
        </div>
        <p class="impl-desc">
          A Kubernetes operator that captures live API activity via audit webhooks and converts it
          into versioned, sanitised YAML in Git. It strips runtime fields to produce stable,
          intent-only manifests, batches writes through a queue, and commits with full authorship
          metadata — giving you an audit trail in Git for every API-level change.
        </p>
        <p class="impl-desc">
          Supports audit-only, human-in-the-loop, and split-ownership modes. Includes automatic
          Secret encryption via SOPS/age. Designed for self-managed clusters (k3s, Talos, k3d).
          Early-stage — not yet recommended for production.
        </p>
        <div class="impl-links">
          <a href="https://github.com/ConfigButler/gitops-reverser" class="impl-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View on GitHub →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="impl-submit">
        <p>
          Building an implementation?
          Open a PR against <a href="https://github.com/reverse-gitops/reversegitops.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">reverse-gitops/reversegitops.dev</a> to add it here.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
